  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine the role of endoscopic ultrasound measurement of
      the primary tumor maximum diameter changes in absolute / relative values in predicting the
      tumor regression after concurrent chemoradiotherapy for rectal cancer.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      We use endoscopic ultrasound to measure the primary tumor maximum diameter changes to predict
      the tumor regression after concurrent chemoradiotherapy for rectal cancer
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
